 {"id":"bd-1q5.15","title":"Inline mode rendering (preserve native scrollback)","description":"Key technical challenge: Render FrankenTUI widgets inline within terminal scrollback without destroying native scroll history. No alternate screen takeover for inline widgets. Supports: inline prompts, inline status displays, inline completions. Must coexist with native terminal output above and below. TRACING: span 'inline.render' with fields: inline_height, scrollback_preserved, render_mode. LOG: INFO for inline mode activation, WARN if scrollback preservation fails. METRICS: gauge inline_active_widgets.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:25.614692993Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:27.793205255Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inline-mode","kernel","ring1","scrollback"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.15","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.15","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-1q5.16","title":"Unit tests: Inline mode scrollback preservation","description":"Unit tests: Inline render does not emit alternate screen sequences. Output below inline widget preserves scrollback. Multiple inline widgets coexist. Resize with inline mode active. LOGGING SPEC: Assert inline.render span. Assert no CSI ?1049h (alternate screen) in output.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:25.743785894Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:27.930928403Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["inline-mode","ring1","test","unit"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.16","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.16","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5.15","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-1q5.17","title":"E2E test: Inline mode in real terminal with scrollback","description":"E2E test: (1) Write 100 lines of output to terminal, (2) Render inline widget, (3) Verify scrollback accessible above widget, (4) Remove widget, verify scrollback intact. Use PTY for deterministic testing. LOGGING SPEC: Assert inline.render span. Assert scrollback_preserved=true.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:25.880999237Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:28.066905611Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["e2e","inline-mode","ring1","test"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.17","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.17","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5.15","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-1q5.18","title":"Cx-everywhere for Ring 1 terminal I/O operations","description":"Every Ring 1 terminal I/O operation (read, write, flush, capability probe) takes &asupersync::Cx. Enables: cooperative cancellation of blocked terminal reads, deadline enforcement on writes, deterministic testing of terminal I/O via FrankenLab. TRACING: span 'terminal.io' with fields: op_type, cx_deadline_remaining_us, cx_cancelled. LOG: WARN if I/O exceeds Cx deadline. METRICS: histogram terminal_io_duration_us{op=read|write|flush}.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:26.015488408Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T17:17:52.994933051Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cross-crate","cx","ring1","terminal-io"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.18","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.18","depends_on_id":"bd-ehk.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-1q5.18","title":"Cx-everywhere for Ring 1 terminal I/O operations","description":"Every Ring 1 terminal I/O operation (read, write, flush, capability probe) takes &asupersync::Cx. Enables: cooperative cancellation of blocked terminal reads, deadline enforcement on writes, deterministic testing of terminal I/O via FrankenLab. TRACING: span 'terminal.io' with fields: op_type, cx_deadline_remaining_us, cx_cancelled. LOG: WARN if I/O exceeds Cx deadline. METRICS: histogram terminal_io_duration_us{op=read|write|flush}.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:26.015488408Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T17:40:48.900570646Z","closed_at":"2026-02-14T17:40:48.900545439Z","close_reason":"Implemented Cx-aware variants for all Ring 1 TerminalSession I/O methods: poll_event_cx, read_event_cx, show_cursor_cx, hide_cursor_cx, set_mouse_capture_cx, size_cx, flush_cx. Each emits tracing span 'terminal.io' with op_type/cx_deadline_remaining_us/cx_cancelled fields. Added terminal_io_{read,write,flush}_stats() metric accessors. 10 new tests. All quality gates pass (fmt, clippy, 1110+24 tests).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cross-crate","cx","ring1","terminal-io"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.18","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.18","depends_on_id":"bd-ehk.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-1q5.19","title":"FrankenTUI error model and graceful degradation","description":"Explicit error model for FrankenTUI: error types (TerminalError, RenderError, LayoutError, WidgetError, ProtocolError), error propagation strategy (Result everywhere, no panics in render path), graceful degradation per error type (terminal capability missing -> fallback rendering, layout error -> previous layout, widget error -> error placeholder widget). TRACING: span 'error.handle' with fields: error_type, degradation_action, recovered. LOG: WARN for recoverable errors, ERROR for unrecoverable. METRICS: counter errors_total{type=terminal|render|layout|widget|protocol}, counter degradation_activations_total{type=...}.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:26.151312418Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T01:56:07.786079605Z","closed_at":"2026-02-14T01:56:07.786061491Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cross-cutting","degradation","error-model"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.19","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1204,"issue_id":"bd-1q5.19","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Error model implemented: 5 domain-specific errors (Terminal/Render/Layout/Widget/Protocol) with DegradationAction mapping, error_type() labels, is_recoverable(), error source chain. 54 tests total. Commit 6849dd80.","created_at":"2026-02-14T01:56:01Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1q5.2","title":"Bayesian diff strategy selection engine","description":"Beta posterior over terminal change rates selects between incremental, full, and deferred diff strategies. Prior: Beta(1,1). Update on each frame with observed change fraction. Strategy selection via expected-loss minimization (not MAP). Evidence terms logged to evidence ledger. TRACING: span 'diff.strategy_select' with fields: posterior_alpha, posterior_beta, change_rate_estimate, selected_strategy, expected_loss, frame_budget_remaining_us. LOG: DEBUG for strategy selection, TRACE for posterior updates. METRICS: counter diff_strategy_selected{strategy=incremental|full|deferred}, histogram diff_posterior_update_duration_us.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T17:59:08.393582605Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T01:42:58.558747736Z","closed_at":"2026-02-14T01:42:58.558729131Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["bayesian","diff","kernel","ring1"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.2","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1201,"issue_id":"bd-1q5.2","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Verified: fully implemented in codebase. Cell (16B, ftui-render/cell.rs), Buffer (2D grid with dirty tracking), Frame (double-buffered), DiffStrategySelector (Beta-binomial Bayesian), Presenter (ANSI state machine with run grouping). All types are production-ready with extensive tests.","created_at":"2026-02-14T01:42:58Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1q5.20","title":"Keyboard and mouse event normalization layer","description":"Event normalization: raw terminal bytes -> structured events (Key, Mouse, Resize, Focus, Paste). Handles: modifier key detection (Ctrl/Alt/Shift), kitty keyboard protocol, mouse modes (normal, button, any, SGR), bracketed paste, focus events. TRACING: span 'event.normalize' with fields: raw_byte_count, event_type, modifiers. LOG: TRACE for raw bytes, DEBUG for normalized events. METRICS: counter events_processed_total{type=key|mouse|resize|focus|paste}.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:08:27.514777703Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T02:13:27.201600495Z","closed_at":"2026-02-14T02:13:27.201581930Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["events","input","kernel","ring1"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.20","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-1q5.20","depends_on_id":"bd-1q5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":1210,"issue_id":"bd-1q5.20","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Complete: Input parser normalization layer fully implemented with 98 tests covering kitty keyboard protocol, SGR mouse, bracketed paste, focus events, modifier detection, and DoS protection. Added tracing instrumentation (event.normalize span, raw_byte_count field, TRACE/DEBUG levels) in 85b9c5a5. Event::event_type_label() added for metrics. Full pipeline: raw bytes → InputParser → Event → SemanticEvent → Action via GestureRecognizer + KeySequenceInterpreter + ActionMapper.","created_at":"2026-02-14T02:13:22Z"}]}
