 {"id":"bd-37a.3","title":"BOCPD resize coalescing engine","description":"Bayesian Online Change-Point Detection (Adams & MacKay 2007) for terminal resize event coalescing. Detects regime transitions (rapid resize stream vs stable). During resize regime, coalesces events; on change-point detection, commits final size. Hazard function: constant rate H(tau)=1/lambda. TRACING: span 'bocpd.update' with fields: run_length_posterior_max, change_point_probability, coalescing_active, resize_count_in_window. LOG: INFO when regime transition detected, DEBUG for posterior updates. METRICS: histogram bocpd_run_length, counter bocpd_change_points_detected_total.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.036464274Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:51.350877498Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["bocpd","resize","ring2","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-37a.3","depends_on_id":"bd-37a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-37a.3","depends_on_id":"bd-37a.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-37a.4","title":"VOI-gated sampling for adaptive decisions","description":"Value-of-Information framework: only sample/measure when the expected information gain exceeds the cost. Applied to: diff strategy probing, layout cache invalidation, animation frame skipping. VOI = E[max_a Q(s,a|new_info)] - max_a Q(s,a|current_info). TRACING: span 'voi.evaluate' with fields: decision_context, voi_estimate, sample_cost, sample_decision. LOG: DEBUG for VOI calculations, TRACE for individual utility estimates. METRICS: counter voi_samples_taken_total, counter voi_samples_skipped_total, histogram voi_estimate_value.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.129153122Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.129153122Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ring2","runtime","sampling","voi"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-37a.4","depends_on_id":"bd-37a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-37a.5","title":"E-process anytime-valid sequential testing","description":"Wealth-based e-processes for anytime-valid statistical tests. Used for: A/B comparison of diff strategies, performance regression detection, anomaly detection in frame times. Test martingale: E_t = prod(e_i). Rejection when E_t >= 1/alpha. No need for fixed sample size. TRACING: span 'eprocess.update' with fields: test_id, wealth_current, wealth_threshold, observation_count, rejected. LOG: INFO when test rejects (significant finding), DEBUG for wealth updates. METRICS: gauge eprocess_wealth{test_id=...}, counter eprocess_rejections_total.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.227560995Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.227560995Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["eprocess","ring2","runtime","testing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-37a.5","depends_on_id":"bd-37a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-37a.6","title":"Command/Subscription effect system with Cx capability threading","description":"Effect system for side effects: Commands (one-shot async effects: file I/O, clipboard, spawn), Subscriptions (ongoing event streams: keyboard, mouse, timer, resize). All effects take &asupersync::Cx for cancellation propagation and deadline enforcement. Structured concurrency: all subscriptions torn down on model shutdown. TRACING: span 'effect.command' with fields: command_type, duration_us, result. span 'effect.subscription' with fields: sub_type, event_count, active. LOG: DEBUG for effect lifecycle, WARN for effect timeout, ERROR for effect panic. METRICS: counter effects_executed_total{type=command|subscription}, histogram effect_duration_us.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.319507101Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:51.487480908Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cx","effects","ring2","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-37a.6","depends_on_id":"bd-37a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-37a.6","depends_on_id":"bd-ehk.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-37a.6","title":"Command/Subscription effect system with Cx capability threading","description":"Effect system for side effects: Commands (one-shot async effects: file I/O, clipboard, spawn), Subscriptions (ongoing event streams: keyboard, mouse, timer, resize). All effects take &asupersync::Cx for cancellation propagation and deadline enforcement. Structured concurrency: all subscriptions torn down on model shutdown. TRACING: span 'effect.command' with fields: command_type, duration_us, result. span 'effect.subscription' with fields: sub_type, event_count, active. LOG: DEBUG for effect lifecycle, WARN for effect timeout, ERROR for effect panic. METRICS: counter effects_executed_total{type=command|subscription}, histogram effect_duration_us.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.319507101Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T17:41:30.084010054Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cx","effects","ring2","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-37a.6","depends_on_id":"bd-37a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-37a.6","depends_on_id":"bd-ehk.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-37a.7","title":"Unit tests: Elm architecture update loop","description":"Unit tests covering: Pure update function (no side effects leak). Message ordering preservation. Batch command execution order. Model version monotonicity. Subscription start/stop lifecycle. LOGGING SPEC: Assert runtime.update and runtime.view spans with correct fields. Assert no ERROR logs during normal operation. Property-based: random message sequences never panic, model version always increases.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.412457880Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-14T04:24:59.963315051Z","closed_at":"2026-02-14T04:24:59.963290055Z","close_reason":"Already implemented: 199 tests in program.rs covering Model trait, Cmd batch/quit/perform, subscription lifecycle, message ordering, deterministic simulator","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["elm","ring2","test","unit"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-37a.7","depends_on_id":"bd-37a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-37a.7","depends_on_id":"bd-37a.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-37a.8","title":"Unit tests: BOCPD resize coalescing","description":"Unit tests covering: Change-point detection on synthetic regime-change data (known change points). Coalescing behavior (N rapid resizes -> 1 committed resize). Hazard function parameter sensitivity. Edge cases: single resize, identical consecutive sizes. LOGGING SPEC: Assert bocpd.update span fields. Assert INFO log on regime transition. Verify bocpd_change_points_detected_total counter.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.505421974Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:57.757206336Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["bocpd","ring2","test","unit"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-37a.8","depends_on_id":"bd-37a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-37a.8","depends_on_id":"bd-37a.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-37a.9","title":"Unit tests: VOI sampling & e-process testing","description":"Unit tests covering: VOI correctly skips low-information samples. VOI correctly triggers sampling when uncertainty is high. E-process wealth accumulation against known signal. E-process type-I error control (under null, wealth stays below threshold with high probability). LOGGING SPEC: Assert voi.evaluate and eprocess.update spans. Property-based: under null hypothesis, rejection rate <= alpha + epsilon over 1000 simulated runs.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:00:23.603964790Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-13T18:05:58.034635728Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["eprocess","ring2","test","unit","voi"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-37a.9","depends_on_id":"bd-37a","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-37a.9","depends_on_id":"bd-37a.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-37a.9","depends_on_id":"bd-37a.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-02-13T18:22:56Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
